Total May Buy Brazil’s Clealco for $1.3 Billion, Estado Reports

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-10-11T10:33:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/total-may-buy-brazil-s-clealco-for-1-3-billion-estado-reports.html
Total SA is the leading contender
for the acquisition of Brazilian sugar and ethanol producer
Clealco Acucar & Alcool SA, a transaction estimated at $1.3
billion, O Estado de S. Paulo reported, citing unidentified
executives from the industry.  India’s  Shree Renuka Sugars Ltd. (SHRS)  and Brazil’s ETH
Bioenergia SA are also in talks to buy Clealco, the newspaper
said. The negotiations are in a final stage, Estado said.  Total didn’t respond to Estado’s resquest for comment.
Renuka and Clealco declined to comment, according to Estado.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helder Marinho in  Sao Paulo  at 
